---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services — Recverse"
  description="Clarity, roadmaps, and pragmatic support for using technology well — from orientation and efficiency to privacy-conscious implementation."
>
  <main class="landing-page landing-page--services">
    <section class="hero section">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Services</p>
          <h1>Use technology intentionally — without overload or guesswork.</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            We help companies and individuals evaluate AI and digital tools in a way that creates
            real relief: less tool chaos, clearer priorities, and a realistic next step.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/en/contact/?topic=Initial%20Consultation">Request an initial consultation</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#services">View service areas</a>
          </div>

          <ul class="hero-points" aria-label="Benefits">
            <li>Practical, not abstract</li>
            <li>Clear priorities instead of overwhelm</li>
            <li>Privacy-conscious in a Swiss/EU context</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-card">
          <div class="card-glow"></div>
          <div class="hero-panel">
            <p class="panel-label">What this is about</p>
            <h2>Less action bias. More clarity, structure, and impact.</h2>
            <p>
              Not every new technology is automatically useful. What matters is what actually saves
              time in your reality, simplifies workflows, and can be implemented in a sustainable way
              with reasonable effort.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-alt" id="when-relevant">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <p class="section-kicker">When this becomes relevant</p>
        <h2>Does any of this sound familiar?</h2>

        <div class="problem-grid">
          <article class="problem-card">
            <p>“We keep hearing about AI, but there is no sensible starting point.”</p>
          </article>

          <article class="problem-card">
            <p>“There are too many tools, but no clear prioritization.”</p>
          </article>

          <article class="problem-card">
            <p>“Our processes take too much time, even though a lot should be more digital by now.”</p>
          </article>

          <article class="problem-card">
            <p>“We want to move forward, but without unnecessary risk or wasted effort.”</p>
          </article>
        </div>

        <p class="section-bridge">
          This is exactly where we help with structure, prioritization, and pragmatic execution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="services">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-kicker">Service areas</p>
        <h2>What we can specifically help you with</h2>
        <p class="body-large section-intro">
          Depending on your starting point, the focus may be orientation, efficiency, prioritization,
          privacy, or ongoing support. Not everything at once — only what truly makes sense for your situation.
        </p>

        <div class="services-grid">
          <article class="service-card">
            <span class="service-tag">Orientation</span>
            <h3>AI and technology onboarding with clarity</h3>
            <p>
              If it is unclear where to begin, we first create structure and overview. We organize
              opportunities, risks, and priorities so they turn into a realistic first step.
            </p>
            <ul class="service-list">
              <li>Evaluation of relevant technologies</li>
              <li>Prioritization by value and effort</li>
              <li>First practical use cases</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/en/contact/?topic=AI%20Onboarding%20/%20Orientation" class="btn btn-secondary service-link">Ask about this topic</a>
          </article>

          <article class="service-card">
            <span class="service-tag">Efficiency</span>
            <h3>Simplify processes and reduce unnecessary friction</h3>
            <p>
              Many workflows still contain manual loops, media breaks, or unnecessary complexity.
              We identify leverage points that create noticeable relief with reasonable effort.
            </p>
            <ul class="service-list">
              <li>Analysis of operational pain points</li>
              <li>Quick wins with immediate day-to-day value</li>
              <li>Pragmatic improvements instead of a large-scale project</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/en/contact/?topic=Brainstorming" class="btn btn-secondary service-link">Discuss efficiency opportunities</a>
          </article>

          <article class="service-card">
            <span class="service-tag">Roadmap</span>
            <h3>Concrete next steps instead of tool chaos</h3>
            <p>
              Good ideas often fail not because of technology, but because of missing structure.
              That is why we translate potential into clear priorities, sensible sequencing,
              and sound decision support.
            </p>
            <ul class="service-list">
              <li>Implementation roadmap with an 80/20 focus</li>
              <li>Step-by-step rollout instead of big bang</li>
              <li>Clear priorities and responsibilities</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/en/contact/?topic=Brainstorming" class="btn btn-secondary service-link">Define a roadmap</a>
          </article>

          <article class="service-card">
            <span class="service-tag">Project execution</span>
            <h3>Support for MVPs, PoCs, and project structure</h3>
            <p>
              Once ideas become real initiatives, they need scope, structure, and realistic execution logic.
              We help set projects up cleanly and move them forward with proper judgment.
            </p>
            <ul class="service-list">
              <li>Structure an AI MVP or PoC</li>
              <li>Sharpen project logic and decision paths</li>
              <li>Reduce scope risk in a controlled way</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/en/contact/?topic=AI%20MVP%20/%20PoC" class="btn btn-secondary service-link">Discuss an MVP or PoC</a>
          </article>

          <article class="service-card">
            <span class="service-tag">Responsibility</span>
            <h3>Privacy-conscious and well-governed usage</h3>
            <p>
              Especially with AI and digital tools, confidentiality, data flows, and sensible usage
              boundaries should be considered early — not only after risks have already appeared.
            </p>
            <ul class="service-list">
              <li>Awareness of Swiss/EU context</li>
              <li>Deliberate handling of sensitive data</li>
              <li>Reduction of unnecessary tool and process risk</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/en/contact/?topic=Website%20Privacy%20Check" class="btn btn-secondary service-link">Ask about privacy-related support</a>
          </article>

          <article class="service-card">
            <span class="service-tag">Ongoing support</span>
            <h3>Continuous sparring and development support</h3>
            <p>
              Moving forward with technology in a sensible way does not require constant new tools.
              It requires regular evaluation, refinement, and support with the next decisions that matter.
            </p>
            <ul class="service-list">
              <li>Recurring review and sparring sessions</li>
              <li>Refinement of priorities and actions</li>
              <li>Support for new questions as they arise</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/en/contact/?topic=Ongoing%20Support" class="btn btn-secondary service-link">Request ongoing support</a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-alt" id="process">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-kicker">Working together</p>
        <h2>How collaboration typically works</h2>

        <div class="process-grid">
          <article class="process-card">
            <div class="step-number">01</div>
            <h3>Initial consultation</h3>
            <p>
              We clarify your starting point, goals, bottlenecks, and the area where pressure is currently highest.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="process-card">
            <div class="step-number">02</div>
            <h3>Current-state assessment</h3>
            <p>
              Relevant topics are prioritized so that not everything gets tackled at once.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="process-card">
            <div class="step-number">03</div>
            <h3>Quick wins & roadmap</h3>
            <p>
              You receive concrete next steps instead of abstract recommendations with no execution value.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="process-card">
            <div class="step-number">04</div>
            <h3>Optional follow-on support</h3>
            <p>
              If needed, we continue to support the next steps — structured, pragmatic, and focused.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="principles">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-kicker">How we work</p>
        <h2>What we value in the way we work</h2>

        <div class="trust-grid">
          <article class="trust-card">
            <h3>Practice over buzzwords</h3>
            <p>
              No trend-following for its own sake — only solutions that create real value in everyday operations.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="trust-card">
            <h3>Realistic implementation</h3>
            <p>
              Recommendations must fit your team, resources, processes, and decision logic.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="trust-card">
            <h3>Clean handling of risk</h3>
            <p>
              Privacy, confidentiality, and unnecessary dependencies are considered early.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="trust-card">
            <h3>Structure before action bias</h3>
            <p>
              Not more parallel workstreams — a clear sequence and sensible priorities.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section cta-section" id="cta">
      <div class="container cta-box">
        <div>
          <p class="section-kicker">Next step</p>
          <h2>Let’s find out what actually makes sense in your situation</h2>
          <p class="body-large">
            In the initial consultation, we clarify where you stand, what should realistically be prioritized,
            and which first step is most likely to create value.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/en/contact/?topic=Initial%20Consultation">Request an initial consultation</a>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/en/">Back to home</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .landing-page--services .problem-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .landing-page--services .services-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .landing-page--services .process-grid,
    .landing-page--services .trust-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .landing-page--services .service-list {
      margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
      padding-left: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--rv-text-soft);
    }

    .landing-page--services .service-list li {
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }

    .landing-page--services .service-link,
    .landing-page--services .service-link:visited {
      margin-top: auto;
      align-self: flex-start;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--rv-text);
    }

    .landing-page--services .service-link:hover,
    .landing-page--services .service-link:focus-visible {
      color: var(--rv-text);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1180px) {
      .landing-page--services .process-grid,
      .landing-page--services .trust-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .landing-page--services .service-link {
        width: 100%;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>